(Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Fifty-six children were taken to Pietermaritzburg hospitals after showing signs of food poisoning while at school, KwaZulu-Natal emergency services said on Friday."The children, aged between 9 and 12, had started showing symptoms of food poisoning," spokesperson Robert Mckenzie said.They were taken to the nearby Phatheni clinic before paramedics transferred them to various hospitals in the Pietermaritzburg area."Four of the children were in a serious condition, the remainder were stable," he said."Investigations are under way which will determine what caused the children to fall sick."24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.